\n\nSubstituting the values of a, b, and D:\nx = (-(-5) ± sqrt(1)) / (2*1)\nx = (5 ± 1) / 2\n\nSo, the two roots are:\nx1 = (5 + 1) / 2 = 6 / 2 = 3\nx2 = (5 - 1) / 2 = 4 / 2 = 2\n\n### Step 4: Verify using Vieta's formulas\nAccording to Vieta's formulas:\n- The sum of the roots x1 + x2 should equal -b/a.\n- The product of the roots x1 * x2 should equal c/a.\n\nVerifying:\n- x1 + x2 = 3 + 2 = 5 = -(-5)/1 = 5 (matches)\n- x1 * x2 = 3 * 2 = 6 = 6/1 = 6 (matches)\n\nBoth conditions are satisfied, confirming that the roots are correct.\n\nAlternatively, we could also try to factor the quadratic equation directly:\nx^2 - 5x + 6 = (x - 2)(x - 3) = 0\n\nThis gives us the roots x = 2 and x = 3, which matches our solution using the quadratic formula.\n\nTherefore, the roots of the equation x^2 - 5x + 6 = 0 are x = 2 and x = 3.\n\nVerify the solution and respond with JSON only."}], 'model': 'llama-3.3-70b-versatile', 'max_tokens': 600, 'temperature': 0.1}}
