oots match the expected values:\nx1 + x2 = 4 + (-1/2) = 7/2\n-b/a = -(-7)/2 = 7/2 (matches)\nx1 * x2 = 4 * (-1/2) = -2\nc/a = -4/2 = -2 (matches)\n\n## Step 7: State final answer\nThe roots of the equation 2x² - 7x - 4 = 0 are x = 4 and x = -1/2.\n\nThe final answer is: $\\boxed{4, -\\frac{1}{2}}$\n\nRewrite as a clear step-by-step explanation following the format in your instructions."}], 'model': 'llama-3.3-70b-versatile', 'max_tokens': 1500, 'temperature': 0.4}}
