g Vieta's formulas\nTo verify our roots, we use Vieta's formulas:\nx1 + x2 = -b/a\n4 + (-1/2) = -(-7)/2\n4 - 1/2 = 7/2\n(8 - 1)/2 = 7/2\n7/2 = 7/2\n\nx1 * x2 = c/a\n4 * (-1/2) = -4/2\n-2 = -4/2\n-2 = -2\n\nBoth Vieta's formulas are satisfied, so our roots are correct.\n\n## Step 5: State final answer\nThe roots of the equation 2x^2 - 7x - 4 = 0 are x = 4 and x = -1/2.\n\nThe final answer is: $\\boxed{4, -\\frac{1}{2}}$\n\nVerify the solution and respond with JSON only."}], 'model': 'llama-3.3-70b-versatile', 'max_tokens': 600, 'temperature': 0.1}}
