oots)\nIf x1, x2 are roots of ax^2 + bx + c = 0:\n- x1 + x2 = -b/a\n- x1 * x2 = c/a\n\n### Completing the Square\nax^2 + bx + c = a(x + b/(2a))^2 + (c - b^2/(4a))\n\n[SOURCE: common_mistakes.md]\n## Algebra Mistakes\n\n### Mistake 1: Wrong sign in quadratic formula\nWRONG: x = (-b ± sqrt(b^2 - 4ac)) / 2   [missing 'a' in denominator]\nCORRECT: x = (-b ± sqrt(b^2 - 4ac)) / (2a)\nAlways: the full denominator is 2a, not 2.\n\n### Mistake 2: Forgetting ± when taking square root\nWRONG: x^2 = 9 → x = 3\nCORRECT: x^2 = 9 → x = ±3 (both +3 and -3)\n\n### Mistake 3: Illegal cancellation\nWRONG: (x^2 + 4) / x = x + 4   [cannot cancel x with x^2]\nCORRECT: (x^2 + 4) / x = x + 4/x\n\n[SOURCE: solution_templates.md]\nSTEP 5 — State final answer\n  x = [x1] or x = [x2]\n\n---\n\nSimilar Past Solved Problems:\n[PAST PROBLEM] Q: Solve the quadratic equation two x squared minus seven x minus four equals zero.\nFind the values of x.\n[PAST ANSWER]  A: 4, -1/2\n\n[PAST PROBLEM] Q: Solve the quadratic equation: two x squared minus seven x minus four equals zero. \nWhat are the values of x?\n[PAST ANSWER]  A: The roots of the equation 2x^2 - 7x - 4 = 0 are x = 4 and x = -1/2.\n\n[PAST PROBLEM] Q: Solve the quadratic equation:\n\n2x² - 7x - 4 = 0\n\nFind the values of x.\n[PAST ANSWER]  A: 4, -1/2\n\nNow solve the problem step by step:"}], 'model': 'llama-3.3-70b-versatile', 'max_tokens': 2000, 'temperature': 0.2}}
